The paper deals with information theory and coding for communication channels, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also presents a coding scheme, which falls under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The paper discusses error detection and correction, which is a topic in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper uses probability theory and statistics to derive bounds, which is a topic in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with interactive communication, which is a topic in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
